  "texts": [
    "Each w t,i in RWKV is a channelwise time decay vector multiplied by the relative position and traced backward from current time as it decays:",
    "where w ∈ (R ≥0) d, with d the number of channels.",
    "We require w to be non-negative to ensure that e w t,i ≤ 1 and the per-channel weights decay backwards in time.",
    "The RWKV model architecture is defined by four fundamental elements that are intrinsic to the timemixing and channel-mixing blocks:",
    "• R: The Receptance vector acts as the receiver of past information."
  ],
